sec.p:
The vector |r→i| is assumed as much smaller than |R→|, and the products of inertia assumed as zeros with respect to the spacecraft body-fixed coordinate. By applying Binomial series expansion and carrying out the expansion till O(1/|R→|3), the first term in the potential energy is given as
(4)Us=-μMsR+μ4R3 {(Isz+Isy+Isz)    -3[Isy+(Isz-Isx)cos(2θ)] }
where Isx, Isy and Isz are the moments of inertia of spacecraft with respect to the spacecraft boy-fixed coordinate; R is the magnitude of the vector |R→|. It is clearly seen that the spacecraft is affected by the gravity effect only when the moments of inertia Isx and Isz are not equal.
